id: pm-95d7
title: Align pm-codex with native ChatGPT/Codex plugin and Apps SDK contracts
description: "Harden the shipped pm-codex bundle as a self-contained, version-coherent native Codex plugin, make supported plugin components and install behavior accurate, and define the separate Apps SDK architecture required for ChatGPT web and public plugin distribution."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[7]: apps-sdk,"area:plugins",chatgpt,codex,distribution,mcp,roadmap
created_at: "2026-07-11T11:10:40.136Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T17:05:03.633Z"
author: codex-native-plugin-research
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "Cached marketplace installs load a self-contained MCP runtime whose version matches the installed plugin without an npx-at-latest startup dependency; only documented plugin components are shipped or claimed; manifest, marketplace, assets, legal metadata, skills, and MCP configuration validate against the then-current official OpenAI contract; cache-layout and fresh-session smokes prove skills and MCP tools load; the ChatGPT lane is resolved by an explicit architecture decision and, if selected, a reachable MCP app with exact tool schemas, output schemas, safety annotations, authentication/privacy controls, developer-mode proof, submission tests, and documented surface support; implementation starts only after explicit approval."
value: "A trustworthy plugin whose native Codex behavior, ChatGPT reach, runtime packaging, permissions, and public distribution claims match the official OpenAI contracts."
why_now: "Official plugin and Apps SDK documentation changed materially in 2026, while the cached pm-codex runtime still falls back to npx at latest and the public docs conflate a local Codex bundle with a ChatGPT app."
parent: pm-doxj
risk: high
confidence: high
expected_result: "pm-codex has an evidence-backed local Codex implementation and an explicit, independently validated path for any ChatGPT app or public plugin scope."
component: plugins/pm-codex
